Almost done. I hope we can get the pull request out by next week. This will also change the CPU implementations as we are using generic code that is equivalent on GPU & CPU. 
One thing: This is a thread specifically about multinomial distribution. This distribution was brought in independently by Eric some time ago and supports CPU/GPU already. So not sure why this issue here is still open. Shouldn't we close it?

@Eshter

For example, assume `MatA` has shape (B, 1, C) and `MatB` also has shape (B, 1, C). Our goal is to get the `ret` of size (B, 1, 1) by dot-multiply the corresponding row-vectors in two matrices.

There are two ways to achieve this:

1) Elementwise multiplication and use `mx.nd.sum`
```python
ret = mx.nd.sum(MatA * MatB, axis=-1, keepdims=True)
```
2) Use `mx.nd.batch_dot`
```python
ret = mx.nd.batch_dot(MatA, MatB, transpose_b=True)
```

OK, do we have a separate issue for the general sampling OPs? I'm going to close it as it's only about multinomial, which has been supported. https://mxnet.incubator.apache.org/api/python/symbol.html#mxnet.symbol.sample_multinomial
